The warfare of funny pictures on internet

How the users of TikTok reacted to the contents shared by Matteo Salvini in the first week of the activity on his official profile?

  • How many contents related to memetic warfare does Google.it return when a user searches â€œmemeâ€?
  • Which kind of sources spread contents about Memetic warfare on Google.it and what is their orientation?
  • Which are the most used keywords in the results about memetic warfare on Google.it and which are the main emerging topics?
  • Which are the cultural backgrounds of Telegram stickers related to Pepe the frog and which graphic elements connect them to different ideologies?
  • Which memes are posted on the r/HongKong subreddit and which
    are their targets?
  • How the users of TikTok reacted to the contents shared by Matteo Salvini in the first week of the activity on his official profile?

The final part attempt to analyze the phenomenon of memification of music and video, as happened a few years ago on Vine. Although TikTok prohibits politics, it is interesting to analyze how an institutional figure (former Minister of the Interior) uses it in a controversial way, talking about this topic. Furthermore, it is interesting to analyse the usersâ€™ reactions to this approach.

Main Findings

The views are always greater than the number of followers, reaching in some case a ration of twenty to one.

A greater engagement was achieved by posting an original content (created by him) and therefore shareable by other people.

Only 6% of the more voted comments openly supports Salvini. These comments are outnumbered by those that harshly criticize him.
